    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 10, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: Referring to your private memorandum of the
                    19th ultimo, relative to Francis Carroll, and to my reply, I now have the honor
                    to inform you that, under date of the 7th instant, he was ordered to be
                    discharged from Fort Lafayette on his parole, to report forthwith, personally,
                    to General Schenck for further order, and that General Schenck has been advised
                    thereof.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, your very obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
